From Chuq Von Rospach Subject Re SHARKS REVIEW Part Left Wings paul Paul Brownlow writes Wood played most of his junior career in He was one of the leading scorers on a mediocre team when he was traded away in He rarely lost a fight and was one of the toughest players in the Wood is fairly small for an enforcer I mean Fleury does a pretty good job and isn't that large but Dody is no Having been witness to three or four of his fights closeup he simply isn't ready to fight at an NHL level assuming that it's his role which is ALL he really showed us in his few games up from if he can pass shoot or skate I never saw much of it All he has is a right fist which isn't bad but at the NHL level the other players are smart enough to grab the thing before he can land anything Once you control that hand he's a fish flopping on the beach and the other player can do just about anything he wants to His entire strategy seemed to be keep the hand out of reach until he found an opening and I never once saw him find an opening worth talking He got neutralized quickly and stomped on a couple of Unless he shows some new tricks in camp he'll be on my career minor leaguer Since this was his first taste of the NHL I expect the Sharks gave it to him so he'd KNOW what he'd have to work on off He needs to get stronger he needs to get more speed and he needs to show some versatility as something else than a simply goond because he wasn't particularly good as a Chuq IMHO Von Rospach ESD Support Training DAL AUX Member SFWA Editor OtherRealms GEnie ALink CHUQ Minor League fans San Jose Giants A San Francisco Giants fans The Stick NOT San Jose Sharks fans New seat TBD